                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">817.00/5198: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Nicaragua</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Munro</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-12-22T11:00:00-05:45">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1927—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>379. My December 21, 3 p.m. The Minister of Interior told me this morning that
                    the Congress was about to adjourn over the holidays and that consequently,
                    pending the necessary study of General McCoy’s electoral project, the Government
                    was about to propose as an emergency measure that the terms of members of the
                    existing electoral boards be extended by congressional action until the new law
                    should be adopted. I declined to approve this procedure on the ground that the
                    Liberals could with some justice claim the right to control the majority of the
                    departmental electoral boards after January 1st unless General McCoy’s project
                    should be approved before that date. I urged rather that Congress be persuaded
                    to remain in session in view of the urgency of this matter and the desirability
                    of early action on the <hi rend="italic">guardia</hi> agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Munro</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
